Name: Jhalak
Short Description: The Indian Cultural Association at The University...
Long Description: The Indian Cultural Association at The University of Texas at Austin would like to thank you for your interest in the 19th annual Jhalak Dance Competition. We invite you to experience the beautiful city of Austin while competing at one of the most unique Bollywood Fusion competitions in the nation! Jhalak removes production and props from the judging criteria, truly cutting the frills from each performance. We do this to ensure that the best team is chosen, based on the best dancing ability demonstrated by each team’s audition.

Name: Aaj Ka Dhamaka
Short Description: The Carolina Tar Heels are ready to bring the DHAM...
Long Description: The Carolina Tar Heels are ready to bring the DHAMAKA to you!!

Name: Infusion
Short Description: Infusion is Pennsylvania State University's premie...
Long Description: Infusion is Pennsylvania State University's premier fusion dance competition holding both Bollywood America Signature Competition and Legends Partner Competition status. Back for its eighth year, Infusion is inviting nine fusion dance teams to compete for cash prizes and points towards Bollywood America and Legends. We hope to spread multiculturalism through dance as well as raise money for Environmental Defense Fund (for ecosystem restoration) and THON (for childhood cancer). After seven successful years in the fusion dance circuit, the Infusion board firmly believes in sincerity, hospitality, and community. Above all, the Infusion management team has come together to organize the HOTTEST fusion dance competition in the nation.

Name: Jhoomti Shaam
Short Description: Hosted by UCLA’s official Bollywood and Hindi-Film...
Long Description: Hosted by UCLA’s official Bollywood and Hindi-Film Dance team, UCLA Nashaa, Jhoomti Shaam has celebrated the South Asian community through expression of art and dance. Now in its 18th year, Jhoomti Shaam will be held on March 7, 2020 in the prestigious Palace Theatre in Los Angeles .  For the past 17 years, Jhoomti Shaam has strived to serve as a beacon of cultural awareness for the South Asian community and its allies. Our competition and dancers, no matter what race, color, creed, or class, understand the cultural misrepresentations of the South Asian community pervasive in our world. Jhoomti Shaam encourages the courage and strength displayed by the stories that dance teams from all over the country bring to our stage. These dancers are committed to sharing their spark of hope with the world, and we are more than humbled to be a part of their journey. After all, Jhoomti Shaam is where stars are born.

Name: Midwest Dhamaka
Short Description: Midwest Dhamaka is the University of Cincinnati’s...
Long Description: Midwest Dhamaka is the University of Cincinnati’s premier Bollywood-fusion dance competition. Currently, we are in our ninth year and we pride ourselves on being, both, a Legends Partner Competition and Bollywood America Official Bid Competition. Each year, we invite eight collegiate Bollywood fusion dance teams from across the nation to compete in Cincinnati. Through Midwest Dhamaka, we are able to promote diversity and inclusion on our campus by sharing our love for South Asian culture. Additionally, we pride ourselves in being a platform that creates for dancers a safe space for expression and collaboration. Finally, this year we are ecstatic to work with Elementz, a non-profit group in Cincinnati, that shares our love for the arts and our community.

Name: Aaja Nachle
Short Description: Aaja Nachle is proud to be BACK and BIGGER than ev...
Long Description: Aaja Nachle is proud to be BACK and BIGGER than ever for its 5th year as a Bollywood Fusion Dance Competition! The competition will be held on February 15th, 2020 at the Marshall Family Performing Arts Center. We are delighted to once again partner with Legends Bollywood Dance Championship as an official Partner Competition and Bollywood America as an official Bid Competition. Dedicated to providing our dancers with the best southern hospitality possible, we guarantee the best year for Aaja Nachle by showcasing the immense talent our South Asian community across the nation holds. By partnering with Ekal Vidyalaya, we hope to raise awareness to eradicate illiteracy in India. #comedance

Name: Tufaan
Short Description: Tufaan Entertainment is a student-run non-profit o...
Long Description: Tufaan Entertainment is a student-run non-profit organization that hosts an annual Fusion dance competition where 9 esteemed teams from across the nation can compete. Witness the storm of the century, as teams compete to conquer the windy city for the 10th year! The winning team receives an entry bid for Bollywood America and Legends, the 2 national Fusion championships.  Tufaan aims to raise funds and awareness for causes important to the South Asian community. Each year, a charity that promotes education through art forms is chosen to be the beneficiary of Tufaan Entertainment's efforts. All proceeds from our efforts will be donated to Shanti Bhavan, a school that educates impoverished children in India. For more information, check out their website www.shantibhavanonline.org.

Name: Maryland Minza
Short Description: Maryland Minza is a national int...
Long Description: Maryland Minza is a national intercollegiate dance competition created to foster cultural awareness and passion for dancing. Minza was co-founded in 2016 at the University of Maryland by Meghana Annadata, Sonia Arya, and Neha Gupta. The word Minza means “star” in Urdu and was chosen to illuminate the essence of performing.

Name: Aag Ki Raat
Short Description: Aag Ki Raat will be held on March 7th, 2020 at the...
Long Description: Aag Ki Raat will be held on March 7th, 2020 at the Ira and Nancy Koger Center for the Arts. This competition is taking place in downtown Columbia, South Carolina - a city filled with history, tradition and wonderful Southern hospitality.  AKR 2020 promises to be bigger and better than ever before! Eight talented Bollywood-fusion teams from around the country will have the opportunity to compete for prize money: $1000 for first place, $500 for second place and $250 for third place.  Please do not hesitate to reach out to this year's Aag Ki Raat Directors, Nikhita Chaubey and Vishnu Menon, with any questions or concerns at uscakr@gmail.com  Thank you and we look forward to your applications!

Name: Tamasha SD
Short Description: San Diego's premiere Bollywood-Fusion dance compet...
Long Description: San Diego's premiere Bollywood-Fusion dance competition. The placing teams at Tamasha will receive points for both Bollywood America and Legends. If you have any questions/concerns about our application process, please reach out to us at registration@tamashasd.com!

Name: Oak City Revolution
Short Description: Oak City Revolution is North Carolina State Univer...
Long Description: Oak City Revolution is North Carolina State University’s premier national collegiate Bollywood-Fusion dance competition that helps celebrates the South-Asian community around us. Located in Raleigh, North Carolina, we pride ourselves on our signature southern hospitality to ensure everyone experiences a warm welcome and stay. Our primary goal is to encourage teams’ passion for dance and appreciation for different cultures, while also fostering a foundation of perseverance and artistic expression, to create a show unlike any other. Mark your calendars because OCR will be taking place on March 21st, 2020!

Name: Aa Dekhen Zara (ADZ)
Short Description: ADZ is UW Madison's largest South Asian Dance comp...
Long Description: ADZ is UW Madison's largest South Asian Dance competition, featuring 8 Bollywood Fusion Teams and 8 Bhangra teams. We are so thrilled to host our largest competition yet as a Bollywood America Official Bid competition and a Legends Partner competition. We are also ecstatic to announce our partnership with Yuwa, an NGO in rural Jharkand that helps break cycles of child poverty, human trafficking, and child marriage. Yuwa uses football (soccer) as a means to teach young women leadership skills, and they are hoping to increase their impact by building a properly functioning school. Right now Yuwa students have classrooms outside, in bathrooms, or wherever space can be found. ADZ 2020 is committed to raising as much money for Yuwa's school as possible. We hope to see you on February 8th in Madison, Wisconsin!

Name: A-Town Showdown
Short Description: A-Town Showdown is the first and finest competitio...
Long Description: A-Town Showdown is the first and finest competition of its kind. The annual intercollegiate dance competition showcases a total of 16 teams — 8 Garba-Raas and 8 Bollywood Fusion teams, competing in their respective categories. We are proud to be partnering with NQAPIA, a philanthropy that works to provide support and leadership to South Asian LGBTQIA+ communities.

Name: Buckeye Mela
Short Description: Buckeye Mela is a national inter-collegiate Bollyw...
Long Description: Buckeye Mela is a national inter-collegiate Bollywood-Fusion and Bhangra dance competition held annually at The Ohio State University in Columbus, OH. This year, the competition will take place on February 01, 2020 at the prestigious Mershon Auditorium on the OSU campus. We are excited to once again be a Legends Bollywood Dance Championship Partner Competition. Buckeye Mela has grown to be The Ohio State University's largest philanthropic South Asian event, and the biggest South Asian dance competition in the Midwest. In our thirteenth year of existence, we guarantee this year's competition to be the best Mela yet!

Name: Jazba
Long Description: Jazba 2020 is an intercollegiate, Bollywood-Fusion dance competition that raises awareness for underprivileged South Asian women by partnering with Women in Need. Winners of this competition receive both trophies and prize money. This year, we are partnered with Legends Bollywood Dance Championship and are a Bollywood America Signature Competition. Winners will thus also win points towards Legends Bollywood Dance Championship and a Bollywood America Bid.

Name: Nachte Raho
Short Description: Nachte Raho is having it's 18th annual competition...
Long Description: Nachte Raho is having it's 18th annual competition at the beautiful Hancher Auditorium in Iowa City, IA.

Name: UGA India Night
Short Description: UGA India Night is a Bollywood-fusion dance compet...
Long Description: UGA India Night is a Bollywood-fusion dance competition anticipated around the nation. It is the largest and most esteemed event held by the UGA Indian Cultural Exchange (UGA ICE). Every year, within the first week of February, the Classic Center graciously hosts more than two thousand people from all over the country.   The first UGA India Night was in held in 1994. For many years it was a talent show for the UGA Indian community. However by 2015, through the efforts of an excellent exec, India Night was an official in-state dance competition featuring bhangra, raas, and Bollywood-fusion teams.  This year, the 26th annual UGA India Night will be a national Bollywood-fusion dance competition. This reputable show is expected to have an attendance of more than two thousand people from all over the country who are expected to be met with warm southern hospitality on the behalf of UGA Indian Cultural Exchange.
